<headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 03 at 4:26PM CDT  by NWS Little Rock</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of north central Izard
and western Fulton Counties through 445 PM CDT...
At 426 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Flint Springs, or 7 miles west of Salem in Fulton County, moving
northeast at 20 mph.
HAZARD...Winds in excess of 30 mph and penny size hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.
Locations impacted include...
Salem in Fulton County...         Oxford...
Viola...                          Bexar...
Byron...                          Flint Springs...
Sturkie...                        Wideman...
Moko...                           Wheeling...
Union...                          Elizabeth...
Salem Airport...                  Mitchell...
Wild Cherry...                    Camp...
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.75 IN
MAX WIND GUST...30 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
